cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CV

This paper proposes a data-driven approach to regularizing embedding layers in deep neural networks. The paper presents theoretical guarantees and empirical results on various tasks related to natural language processing and recommender systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper also mentions the transformer and BERT models, which are commonly used in the field of natural language processing, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) could also be relevant sub-categories.
